1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a reactive navigation strategy for Micro Aerial Vehicles (MAVs) using Inertial Measurement Unit (IMU) and monocular feedback. This falls under the domain of robotics and hence, cs.RO is the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses monocular feedback for ego motion estimation. This involves image processing and feature extraction, which are core areas of computer vision. Hence, cs.CV is the second most likely sub-category. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses an Iterated Extended Kalman Filter (IEKF) scheme for state estimation. Kalman Filters are widely used in machine learning for state estimation and prediction. Hence, cs.LG is the third most likely sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a reactive navigation strategy for MAVs, which involves control and stabilization of the vehicle. This falls under the domain of systems and control. Hence, cs.SY is the fourth most likely sub-category. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel approach for ego motion estimation using direct and tight fusion of IMU measurements with monocular feedback.
